CircleCI is failing due to some package hash mismatch:

```
THESE PACKAGES DO NOT MATCH THE HASHES FROM THE REQUIREMENTS FILE. If you have updated the package versions, please update the hashes. Otherwise, examine the package contents carefully; someone may have tampered with them.
    click==6.6 from https://pypi.python.org/packages/1c/7c/10b4132dd952b6a04e37626258825b8aa8c1eb99545f2eb26a77c21efb55/click-6.6-py2.py3-none-any.whl#md5=ded5bf44698fd7def254d5cb9e5ad0b3 (from -c requirements/constraints.txt (line 13)):
        Expected sha256 cc6a19da8ebff6e7074f731447ef7e112bd23adf3de5c597cf9989f2fd8defe9
             Got        fcf697e1fd4b567d817c69dab10a4035937fe6af175c05fd6806b69f74cbc6c4
```

I believe @mythmon is working on a bug right now related to the build process
